# Collected Observation of Hilo

In an attempt to simply find a verication module for the game Hilo on BC.games, neither the provably fair page nor the 3rd party checkers had one. But when going into the game itself and using the help modal, I was able to discover the on-site verifier which happened to provide a breakdown of how the cards were caluclated and as far as the game result calculation is concerned, it appears to be identical. Granted, the hash calculations are different, but they both use a Rounds generation to calculate each card. However, it does seem a bit confusing how the information is presented at the end but it seems like perhaps the table can tell us what the default order of cards are. Interestingly, as later discovered, the HiLo checker on Stake produces the same result, but only for the first round, actually every round, but in terms of the cards themselves, the results are different (so calculation for the HMAC hash is the same but not the actualy result)

Below is simply for reference for how the checker on the site appears to work:
